==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parturition
<hw>Par`tu*ri"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parturitio</ets>, fr. <ets>parturire</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>parturition</ets>. See <er>Parturient</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of bringing forth, or being delivered of, young; the act of
giving birth; delivery; childbirth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is brought forth; a birth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parturitive</ent>⟦br⟧
